public class CommonElements {
  of main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr1 = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
        int[] arr2 = {4, 5, 6, 7, 8};

        for (int i = 0; i < arr1.length; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < arr2.length; j++) {
                if (arr1[i] == arr2[j]) {
                    System.out.print(arr1[i] + " ");
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```
This program uses two nested loops to iterate through both arrays. For each element in the first array, it checks if it is equal to any element in the second array. If it is, it prints out the common element.

Note that this program has a time complexity of O(n^2), where n is the length of the shorter array, because it uses nested loops to iterate through both arrays. This may not be efficient for large arrays.

